Q37. What frameworks have you used and how do you choose between them?\
\
A: Primarily LangGraph and LangChain. LangGraph for stateful, cyclic, production-grade\
agent workflows \'97 explicit control over state and routing. LangChain for chains, tool\
wrappers, and retrieval components. CrewAI for quick role-based prototyping but not for\
complex production workflows due to less control. LlamaIndex for retrieval-heavy,\
document-centric workflows.\
\
Example:\
    Use LangGraph when:  workflow has loops, conditional routing, HITL, persistent state\
                         e.g., a triage agent that retries diagnosis if confidence is low\
\
    Use CrewAI when:     quick prototype, simple role-based delegation, no complex state\
                         e.g., "researcher + writer" demo in a hackathon\
\
    Use LlamaIndex when: the core value is document retrieval and knowledge grounding\
                         e.g., Q&A over 10,000 internal runbooks\
